---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { totalIdeas, clusters } from '../data/clusters.js';
const path = '/about/';
const collectionCount = clusters.length;

const honest = [
  'Demand signals come from observable behaviour: searches, communities, existing spend, not wishful thinking.',
  'Difficulty and time estimates assume a competent solo builder, and we say plainly when something is genuinely hard.',
  'Some outbound tool links are affiliate links. They never change which tools we recommend.',
];
---
<Base
  title="About ideeeas, validated ideas, openly reasoned"
  description="Why ideeeas exists: a growing, honest library of validated startup and side-project ideas with the reasoning shown, not hidden."
  path={path}
>
  <article class="wrap-narrow py-24 sm:py-28">
    <!-- Folio header -->
    <div class="reveal in eyebrow eyebrow-pill"><span class="dot"></span> About the register</div>
    <h1 class="reveal in mt-6 font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-semibold text-text leading-[1.05] tracking-[-0.025em]">
      A counted library of <span class="serif-i">validated</span> ideas, openly reasoned.
    </h1>
    <p class="reveal in mt-6 text-lg text-soft leading-relaxed">
      The hard part of building something was never the building, it was choosing what to build. The internet is full of "100 business ideas" lists that are really just nouns with the word "app" attached. None of them tell you whether anyone actually wants the thing, how hard it is to make, or how it earns.
    </p>

    <!-- Register stat row -->
    <div class="reveal mt-12 flex flex-wrap items-stretch gap-x-10 gap-y-6 border-y border-edge py-7">
      <div>
        <div class="legend">Entries</div>
        <div class="mt-2 font-mono tabular-nums text-3xl font-medium text-text">{totalIdeas}</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hidden sm:block w-px self-stretch bg-edge"></div>
      <div>
        <div class="legend">Collections</div>
        <div class="mt-2 font-mono tabular-nums text-3xl font-medium text-text">{collectionCount}</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hidden sm:block w-px self-stretch bg-edge"></div>
      <div>
        <div class="legend">Cadence</div>
        <div class="mt-2 font-mono text-3xl font-medium text-text">Weekly</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- S.01 The problem -->
    <section class="reveal mt-16">
      <div class="legend">S.01 &nbsp; THE PROBLEM</div>
      <h2 class="mt-4 font-display text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold text-text tracking-[-0.02em]">Idea spam is not a shortage of ideas</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-soft leading-relaxed">
        There has never been a shortage of ideas, only a shortage of ideas worth your months. A list of a thousand prompts is noise. What a builder needs is a smaller set of entries that have already survived a hard look at demand, difficulty, and money.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="rule my-14"></div>

    <!-- S.02 The method -->
    <section class="reveal">
      <div class="legend">S.02 &nbsp; THE METHOD</div>
      <h2 class="mt-4 font-display text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold text-text tracking-[-0.02em]">Every idea, the same five answers</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-soft leading-relaxed">
        ideeeas is the opposite of an idea-spam list. Every entry is structured the same way: a real demand signal, an honest difficulty rating, a specific monetisation path, a realistic time to MVP, and the single first step you should take to validate it before writing a line of code.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-soft leading-relaxed">
        The library currently holds {totalIdeas} ideas across {collectionCount} collections, and it grows every week. Ideas are starting points, not promises. The value is in the reasoning, so you can adapt each one to your own skills, budget, and market.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="rule my-14"></div>

    <!-- S.03 How it stays honest -->
    <section class="reveal">
      <div class="legend">S.03 &nbsp; HOW IT STAYS HONEST</div>
      <h2 class="mt-4 font-display text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold text-text tracking-[-0.02em]">No fluff, and no hidden incentives</h2>
      <ul class="mt-8 list-none pl-0">
        {honest.map((item, i) => (
          <li class="flex gap-5 border-t border-edge py-5">
            <span class="legend shrink-0 pt-0.5">{String(i + 1).padStart(2, '0')} <span style="color:color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-fog) 55%, var(--color-term))">/ {String(honest.length).padStart(2, '0')}</span></span>
            <p class="text-soft leading-relaxed">{item}</p>
          </li>
        ))}
        <li class="border-t border-edge"></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Closing CTA -->
    <p class="reveal mt-14">
      <a href="/ideas/" class="spark-link font-semibold">Browse the full idea library &rarr;</a>
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
